# Trivy allowlist for known/accepted CVEs (PETPLAT-105).
#
# One CVE ID per line. Only add an entry here after reviewing the scan
# report artifact (uploaded by build-push.yml as "trivy-{service}") and
# confirming the finding is a false positive or genuinely accepted risk —
# never add an entry just to make a failing build pass.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX
#
# Reviewed 2026-07-09, genai-service build (SHA bff2681): 5 CRITICAL findings
# in dependencies pulled in by the base Spring Petclinic template's pom.xml
# (Tomcat embedded server, BouncyCastle, Spring Boot itself). The real fix is
# bumping those dependency versions, but the application repo is read-only
# per project convention — accepted as known risk for this portfolio project
# rather than blocking the pipeline indefinitely.
CVE-2026-41293
CVE-2026-43512
CVE-2026-43515
CVE-2025-14813
CVE-2026-40976
